        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> FOCUS ITEMS HERE (AND MORE)</P><P>From the test server: <BR>Magicians: Please check for new spell scrolls, available for testing in the Bazaar.  Everyone else: Magicians can summon focus items! </P><P>Note: Just to clarify - This does not mean that focus Items are Mage-Summonable-Only forever, nor are these the only kinds that will be out there. These spells will be one of many ways they enter the world.</P><P>We also Cleaned up riposte code. Everything should still riposte as it always has, except for Pets are now more likely to avoid NPC ripostes. (Including Flaming Sword/Rage/Hammer type pets.)</P><P>As an experiment: Wizards have an inherent chance to score a critical blast after 11, modeled after Warrior inherent criticals. (This critical shouldn't impact/devalue/adversely effect existing AA crit skills.) </P><P>Some research on the various forums has garnered us some preliminary information on how the focus items work. </P><P></P><P>Details for the Mages:</P><P>On test the first practical rollout of the spell caster Focus items is underway and they are all summoned no_rent mage items. Its worth noting that these are not the only focus items, but for all intents and purposes these will be the easiest to obtain for quite some time until they add in better ones to existing drop-tables.</P><P>Starting at level 4 and every spell level after that a Mage can summon: </P><P>Choker 4, 24, 50 <BR>Mantle 8, 29, 51 <BR>Bauble (range) 12, 34, 52 <BR>Ring 16, 39, 53 <BR>Bracer 20, 44, 54 <BR>These have lesser, normal, and greater effect versions of : </P><P>Conservation (Mana cost reduction) <BR>Diuturnity (Spell duration) <BR>Destruction (Damage increase) <BR>Pernicity (Spell casting haste) <BR>Abatement (Lower aggro)</P><P>Qhue of Tunare had this to say from his tests:</P><P>The mid 40s bracer gives about a 10% increase in damage (my 675 nuke was hitting for 742) I'm guessing the level 50+ nuking bracer will add maybe 15%?</P><P>So the mage-summoned itesm seem to be somewhere in the 10-15% reduction in mana cost, casting time, increase in nuke etc. </P><P>I imagine the uber-loot focus items from NPC drops will be in the 20-30% range.</P><P>Exciting changes all round!</P><P><BR>All I can say is wow!  Makes me want to start up my mage again.</P><P>Aiaka Masaki<BR>Lvl 45 Nerfomancer Supreme<BR>"Now you shall see the power of a fully armed and operational NERF BAT!"<BR>Wild Hunt on Zeb</font></td>

