        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Ya know after thinking about this one again, i actually feel for mages with this spell line.  One, its going to be a major nuisance to them, much like summoning mod rods are currently.  Secondly, this is a push away from what i perceive to be desired by most mages - increased damage output, most likely by enhancing their pets.</P><P>Unless VI does something to address mage damage outputs on hi end encounters, they'll fall in as a secondary utility class on raids and such.  These focus items i think are only a further push in that direction.  In the end, i anticipate the mage community adding this one to the list of  things they bitch about - aka "all we do is poop out rods, coth and summon focus items"</P><P>Lastly, a previous posted hit the nail on the head.  These items will most likely be vastly inferior to the actual dropped items from mob and npc encounters.  For example, mages get a summoned haste item.  Sounds great, but other than handing this over to their pets, how often is a mage asked for a muzzle from a tank or any melee for that matter?  Almost never.....</P><P><a  href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675">Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
